HEADWORD: Abdominales
<hw>Ab*dom`i*na"les</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n. pl.</pos>
<ety>[NL., masc. pl.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A group including
the greater part of fresh-water fishes, and many marine ones, having the
ventral fins under the abdomen behind the pectorals.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

